    "actor": "https://uofa.net/synth/actor/nagaraja-credibility-team",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All 13 V&V 40 credibility factors were assessed. Twelve of thirteen factors met or exceeded the required gradation level. The single below-requirement factor (Test conditions, achieved Gradation 2 vs. required Gradation 3) reflects the use of a single ASTM F1717 configuration, which is consistent with regulatory expectations for this device class and does not materially undermine confidence in the model's predictive validity for the stated COU. The quantitative output comparison (E/uval < 1.96 for all three QoIs; percent differences <10%) provides direct evidence of model adequacy. The overall credibility assessment supports acceptance of the FEA modeling framework for the intended regulatory submission.",
